# Presentation Layer Rules

## Design Tokens (Non-negotiable)
- ALWAYS use `AppColors` or `AppTheme` for colors
- NEVER use direct `Colors.*` (will be flagged)

## Logging
- NEVER use `print()` or `debugPrint()` in production code
- ALWAYS use `developer.log()` from `dart:developer`

## State Management
- Use BLoC pattern (`Bloc<Event, State>`)
- Use `emit()` instead of `yield`
- Never mutate state directly -- always emit new state
- Check `mounted` before `setState()` in async callbacks

## Async
- Always use `async`/`await`, never `.then()` chains
- Always handle errors in async operations with try-catch

## Philosophy
- "Doors, not badges" -- authentic contributions, not gamification
- Technology enhances real-world experience, doesn't replace it
